The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Statistical highlights
                                                   Statistical highlights
                      
	 Sri Lanka will be the 12th country to host a Twenty20 International when they take on India at the R. Premadasa Stadium in Colombo on Tuesday.         
	 India and Sri Lanka have never played each other in T20 Internationals.         
	 Sri Lanka have played 12 T20 Internationals while India have played 10.         
	 Sanath Jayasuriya has the unique distinction of hitting the most sixes (13) and conceding the most sixes (9) for Sri Lanka in T20 Internationals.         
	 For India Yuvraj Singh has hit the maximum of 15 sixes.         
	 The highest score made by an Indian in T20 Internationals is 75 by Gautam Gambhir.         
	 The highest score made by a Sri Lankan in T20 Internationals is 88 by Sanath Jayasuriya.           COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                   
